<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,786,1935]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,401,1589,1615]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">ETYMOLOGY:</emphasis>
This species is named in honor of our friend and colleague, the late Dr. James Stephen “Steve” Ashe, who was the collector of the 
<typeStatus box="[691,794,1629,1655]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">holotype</typeStatus>
and a significant number of other Central American 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Solier" authorityYear="1834" box="[151,270,1669,1695]" class="Insecta" family="Zopheridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Zopherini">Zopherini</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,786,1935]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,277,1709,1735]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Notes:</emphasis>
This species is probably the sister species to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Garcia-Paris, Coca-Abia, &amp; Parra-Olea" authorityYear="2000" box="[823,932,1710,1735]" class="Insecta" family="Zopheridae" genus="Noserus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="doyeni">
<emphasis box="[823,932,1710,1735]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">S. doyeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which is restricted to higher elevations of 
<collectingRegion box="[151,301,1749,1775]" country="Mexico" name="Nuevo Leon" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Nuevo León</collectingRegion>
. The two species are restricted to sky islands in the Sierra Madre 
<collectingRegion box="[1083,1182,1749,1775]" country="Democratic Republic of the Congo" name="Orientale" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Oriental</collectingRegion>
, and are divided by a considerable distance of unsuitable habitat.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,786,1935]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
No biological information is present on the label data. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Foley &amp; Ivie" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName="Garcia-Paris, Coca-Abia, and Parra-Olea" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[851,1036,1830,1855]" class="Insecta" family="Zopheridae" genus="Sesaspis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="doyeni">
<emphasis box="[851,1036,1830,1855]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Sesaspis doyeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the most closely related species, has been reported under the loose bark of dead pine trees (
<taxonomicName box="[844,952,1869,1895]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[844,911,1870,1895]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Pinus</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[952,962,1870,1895]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">)</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Garcia-Paris, M. &amp; G. Parra-Olea &amp; M. Coca-Abia" box="[978,1264,1869,1895]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="144 - 155" refId="ref39091" refString="Garcia-Paris, M., G. Parra-Olea &amp; M. Coca-Abia (2001) A new species of Noserus (Coleoptera: Zopheridae) from Mexico. Pan-Pacific Entomologist, 77, 144 - 155." type="journal article" year="2001">
García-París 
<emphasis box="[1135,1194,1870,1895]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">et al.</emphasis>
2001
</bibRefCitation>
), and this species probably inhabits a similar high elevation pine-oak forest ecosystem.
</paragraph>
